etomica.space

Class BoundaryRectangular

  • java.lang.Object
    • etomica.space.Boundary
      • etomica.space.BoundaryRectangular
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IBoundary, java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BoundaryRectangularNonperiodic, BoundaryRectangularPeriodic, BoundaryRectangularPore, BoundaryRectangularSlit

    public abstract class BoundaryRectangular
extends Boundary
    Boundary that is in the shape of a rectangular parallelepiped. Periodicity in each direction is specified by subclass.
    See Also:

    • Method Detail

      • getBoxSize

        public IVector getBoxSize()
        Returns a vector with elements equal to the lengths of the edges of the boundary. The returned Vector does not represent the values internally, so manipulation of the vector has no effect on this BoundaryRectangular instance.

      • updateDimensions

        protected void updateDimensions()

      • setBoxSize

        public void setBoxSize(IVector v)
        Sets the size and shape of the rectangular boundary. Values are copied, so manipulation of the given vector has no subsequent effect on this Boundary instance.

      • volume

        public double volume()
        Returns the "volume" of the rectangular region defined by this Boundary. For a 2D and 1D spaces, this volume is actually an area and length, respectively.

      • getEdgeVector

        public IVector getEdgeVector(int d)
        Description copied from interface: IBoundary
        Returns the vector that defines the edge of this boundary for the given dimension. All vectors returned by this method can be considered to originate from one corner.

      • imageOrigins

        public double[][] imageOrigins(int nShells)
        Returns a set of image origins for a set of periodic image shells. The returned array is of dimension [(2*nShells+1)^D][D], where D is the dimension of the space.
        Specified by:
        imageOrigins in class Boundary
        Parameters:
        nShells - the number of shells of images to be computed
